a, M. A., Johnson, R. M., &amp; Smith, T. D. (2021). Analyzing non-normal data distributions using generalized linear models. <em>Journal of Applied Statistics</em>, <em>48</em>(6), 1193–1212.</p><p class="ref-entry">Herndon, M., &amp; Waggoner, C. (2021). Building resilience: Reducing the impact of adverse childhood experiences. <em>Dimensions</em>, <em>49</em>(1), 28–33.</p><p class="ref-entry">Howard, S., &amp; Johnson, B. (2000). What makes the difference? Children and teachers talk about resilient outcomes for children “at risk.” <em>Educational Studies</em>, <em>26</em>(3), 321–337. https://doi.org/10.1080/03055690050137132</p><p class="ref-entry">Khodabandeh, F., Khalilzadeh, M., &amp; Hemati, Z. (2018). Adverse childhood experiences, self-esteem, and aggression in male forensic clients. <em>Journal of Interpersonal Violence</em>, <em>33</em>(6), 917–935.</p><p class="ref-entry">Long, S., &amp; Evans, C. (2021). <em>Promoting resilience-informed care: A practical guidance resource for frontline workers in family-based care</em>. Better Care Network. https://bettercarenetwork.org/sites/default/files/2021-10/Product%20100.11_Promoting%20Resilience%20Informed%20Care%20Guidance%20Final%2024Sept2021.pdf</p><p class="ref-entry">Maughan, B., &amp; McCarthy, G. (1997). Childhood adversities and psychosocial disorders. <em>British Medical Bulletin</em>, <em>53</em>(1), 156–169. https://doi.org/10.1093/oxfordjournals.bmb.a011597</p><p class="ref-entry">McKelvey, L. M., Saccente, J. E., Swindle, T. M., &amp; Adair, L. S. (2018). Association between adverse childhood experiences and educational outcomes in early adolescence. <em>Child: Care, Health and Development</em>, <em>44</em>(3), 430–437.</p><p class="ref-entry">Morgan, M., Rochford, S., &amp; Sheehan, A. (2016). <em>Adversity in childhood: Outcomes, risk and resilience</em>. Centre for Effective Services.</p><p class="ref-entry">Nijs, L., &amp; Nicolaou, G. (2021). Flourishing in resonance: Joint resilience building through music and motion. <em>Frontiers in Psychology</em>, <em>12</em>. https://doi.org/10.3389/fpsyg.2021.666702</p><p class="ref-entry">Ortiz, R. (2019). Building resilience against the sequelae of adverse childhood experiences: Rise up, change your life, and reform health care. <em>American Journal of Lifestyle Medicine</em>, <em>13</em>(5), 470–479. https://doi.org/10.1177/1559827619839997</p><p class="ref-entry">Phakakorn, S., et al. (2018). Health disparities among ethnic minority women in northern Thailand: A cross-sectional survey. <em>BMC Public Health</em>, <em>18</em>(1), 670. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12889-018-5579-x</p><p class="ref-entry">Phakakorn, S., et al. (2019). Housing conditions and health of ethnic minority populations in northern Thailand. <em>PLoS ONE</em>, <em>14</em>(2), e0211861. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0211861</p><p class="ref-entry">Ratanasuwan, W., et al. (2020). Ethnic disparity in maternal mortality in Thailand: A case-control study. <em>Reproductive Health</em>, <em>17</em>(1), 24. https://doi.org/10.1186/s12978-020-0875-6</p><p class="ref-entry">Tanyu, M., Spier, E., Pulizzi, S., Rooney, M., Sorenson, I., &amp; Fernandez, J. (2020). <em>Improving education outcomes for students who have experienced trauma and/or adversity</em>. OECD.</p><p class="ref-entry">Walker, V. S., &amp; Walsh, J. (2015). <em>Understanding the importance of creating positive school climates to support students facing adversity and trauma</em>. National Center on Safe Supportive Learning Environments. https://safesupportivelearning.ed.gov/sites/default/files/NCSSLE-Trauma-Adversity-Brief-508.pdf</p>
